Mourners sobbed and shook their heads in disbelief

Based on official sources, an estimated 45,000 people filed through, and the flow of mourners continued into the night.
An organ and piano alternated dirges.
Sakharov died Thursday alone in his study at the age of 68, apparently of a heart attack, ending a three-decade fight against the jailing of innocent people, for free emigration, for disarmament and other causes.
Sakharov's widow Yelena Bonner, pleased authorities were not turning people away, praised them for being "very democratic."
One man, Sergei Kosykh, brought his 7-year-old daughter along.
